25/06/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A two-day meeting of the Peace Implementation Council's political directors began in Sarajevo on Thursday (24 June). 
The Office of the High Representative said the session will focus on issues related to the unification of Mostar, as well as on the realisation of measures outlined in the European Commission's Feasibility Study for BiH. 
Progress made in educational reform and efforts to join NATO's Partnership for Peace programme will be also discussed. 
(OHR Sources, PBS BiH - 24/06/04)
